      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl5-requirements",
      "rationale": "The primary QOI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) is the direct clinical surrogate for chronic hemolysis and is the quantity specified in the regulatory submission requirements. Secondary QOIs (shear stress distribution, exposure time histograms) are also validated and directly inform the hemolysis model inputs. QOI relevance level 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl5-requirements",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments use the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the same geometry as the COU device — operated at the identical 5 flow-speed combinations specified in the COU. Blood analog fluid (glycerin-water mixture) viscosity and density matched to physiological values within 3%. Validation activity relevance level 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
