      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored via normalized residuals (< 1e-6 for all transport equations) and global integral quantities (NIH, torque) monitored to confirm steady-state. Round-off error assessed via double-precision arithmetic; magnitude < 0.01% of discretization error. Solver error level 4 achieved, exceeding MRL 5 minimum requirement of level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-mrl5-requirements",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup reviewed by an independent CFD analyst not involved in the original setup. Checklist-based review covers boundary condition assignment, material property specification, turbulence model selection, and hemolysis model parameter inputs. Two minor discrepancies identified and corrected prior to final runs. Use error level 3 achieved and meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-mrl5-requirements",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence closure and the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model are justified against published literature for blood pump flows. Sensitivity analysis of hemolysis model exponents (alpha, beta, C) performed via Monte Carlo; NIH predictions are most sensitive to the shear stress exponent (alpha). Alternative hemolysis models (Bludszuweit, Zhang) evaluated; predictions within 18% of primary model. Model form level 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
