      "rationale": "All model input parameters (fluid viscosity, density, hematocrit, hemolysis model constants, turbulence intensity at inlet) characterized with probability distributions derived from experimental measurements and published literature. Monte Carlo sampling (N=2000) propagates full input uncertainty to NIH predictions. 95% prediction interval reported. Model inputs level 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
